gomodel:SYNGO_4664  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Supplementary Fig. 1a\nThe subcellular localization of Shrm4 was first investigated in cultured rat hippocampal neurons at 18 days in vitro (DIV) by immunostaining and found colocalization with presynaptic (Bassoon) and postsynaptic markers of excitatory (PSD-95) and inhibitory (GABAAb3) synapses (Supplementary Fig. 1a).\n\nSupplementary Fig. 1b; Supplementary Table 1\nBy using electron microscopy and post-embedding immunogold methods with an anti-Shrm4 antibody2, gold nanoparticles were identified in pre and post-synaptic areas and along dendrites (Supplementary Fig. 1b; Supplementary Table 1).\n\nSupplementary Fig. 1c\nBiochemical fractionation of adult rat brain hippocampi and cortices revealed enrichment of Shrm4 in the postsynaptic density (PSD) fraction further confirming its presence at synapses (Supplementary Fig. 1c).\n\nFig. 1c; Supplementary Fig. 1e\nMoreover, direct stochastic optical reconstruction microscopy (dSTORM) of 14DIV hippocampal neurons revealed that Shrm4 and GABABRs co-cluster in neurons (Fig. 1c; Supplementary Fig. 1e).. Experimental description: From M&M\nPrimary hippocampal neurons were prepared from Wistar E18 rat brains and plated onto coverslips coated with poly-D-lysine (0.25 mg/ml) at 75,000 per well for immunochemistry, or 300,000 per well for GST pull-down, co-immunoprecipitation and lentivirus infection\n\nShrm4 antibody @ PMID:17009331" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2022-06-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4664" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

